description: Details of reserved matters (scale, external appearance, landscaping, layout of buildings and distribution of land uses) in respect of Phase 3C (Development Zone RS-4 South), pursuant to condition 3 of planning permission 2021/0414 dated 28/02/2022 for the Battersea Power Station development for the restoration, extension, alterations and conversion of the Power Station building and demolition of other buildings and development of the land surrounding the Power Station to provide a mix of uses and open space and landscaping works. An Environmental Statement was submitted with the first outline planning permission (ref:2009/3575) and Section 73 application 2021/0414 was accompanied by an Environmental Statement Addendum.
subdivision_of_building: Not applicable as the site is vacant.
decision_conditions:
Condition : 1 - n accordance with
The development shall be carried out in accordance with the reports, specifications and drawings detailed [... ] 
Reason: To ensure a satisfactory standard of development and to allow the local planning authority to review any potential changes to the scheme.
Condition : 2 - Fire safety and evacuation
Prior to the commencement of development, except for demolition to slab level, a Fire Safety and Evacuation Strategy shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority and the development shall only be carried out in accordance with those approved details. 
Reason: To ensure that adequate arrangements are made for fire safety in accordance with Local Plan policy LP27 and London Plan policies D5 and D12.
Condition : 3 - Trees
Notwithstanding the details in the approved documents, prior to the implementation of any landscaping features, a tree species planting plan shall be submitted to and be approved in writing by the local planning authority. This shall include details of the expected maximum height of each tree species and the spread of their root systems. The tree planting shall therefore be carried out and maintained in accordance with the approved details.
Reason: In the interest of design quality and visual amenity in accordance with Local Plan policies LP1 and LP56.
Condition : 4 - Playspace
Notwithstanding the details shown on the approved plans and set out in the supporting documents, prior to the occupation of the development details of the play space, equipment and street furniture shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. This shall include details of the management and maintenance, including measures to ensure surface and equipment meet relevant British Standards, full details of the regular inspection and maintenance programme to be implemented to maintain access and safety and the anticipated life span before replacement. The development shall be implemented in accordance with the approved details and retained thereafter for the lifetime of the development, unless otherwise approved in writing by the local planning authority. 
Reason: To provide public access to play and recreation facilities in accordance with Local Plan policies LP19, LP20 and to meet the requirements for the provision of play and informal recreation for children and young people in accordance with London Plan policy S4.
Condition : 5 - Senior living units
In accordance with the approved drawings, the use of buildings PP3 and PP4 shall be restricted to Use Class C3 (dwellinghouses). Residential occupation of PP3 shall be restricted to persons aged 55 years and over and the housing units within PP3 may not be used for persons under this age without the prior written consent of the local planning authority.
The development shall then be carried out in accordance with the approved details unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority.
Reason: The playspace and cycle parking provision within the development are based on PP3 being used as senior housing and would need to be increased if PP3 is used for unrestricted residential accommodation within Use Class C3, to meet the requirements of Local Plan policies LP19 and LP51 and London Plan policies S4, H13 and T5.
Condition : 6 - Community hub
Notwithstanding the indicative details in the approved documents:
a)	prior to the commencement of above ground works, details of the community hub shall be submitted to the local planning authority and be approved in writing, including but not limited to details of layout and any specific operational requirements linked to the operator, such as any additional ventilation, access or waste/recycling requirements. It is necessary to submit this prior to implementation to ensure that the details align with the submission of the community hub specification required by Schedule 10 of the S106 agreement and to determine whether any amendments will be required to accommodate the operational requirements.
b)	Prior to occupation of Phase 3C, details of the community hub entrance shall be submitted to the local planning authority and be approved in writing. This shall include details of the layout, shopfront and signage.
Reason: To ensure a high quality development and in the interests of the appearance of the locality, and to secure a well-managed community facility which will meet the needs of existing and new residents in line Local Plan policies LP1, LP8 and LP17.
Condition : 7 - Retention of design team
The original design team (including the architects and landscape designers) shall be retained to assist in the detailed design of the exterior of the development and to monitor the design quality of the development through to completion, including the landscaping, unless otherwise approved in writing by the local planning authority. 
Reason: To maintain the design quality of the development through to the completion of the development, in the interest of the visual amenity of the area, in accordance with London Plan policy D4. 
Condition : 8 - Non-road mobile machinery
All non-road mobile machinery (NRMM) used during the course of the development that is within the scope of the Greater London Authority 'Control of Dust and Emissions during Construction and Demolition' Supplementary Planning Guidance (SPG) dated July 2014, or any subsequent amendment or guidance, shall comply with the emission requirements therein. 
Reason: To manage and prevent further deterioration of existing low quality air across London in accordance with Local Plan policy LP14 and London Plan policy SI1.
Condition : 9 - Satellite dishes
Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (or any Order revoking, amending or re-enacting that Order) no satellite dishes, telecommunications masts, antennas or equipment or associated structures, shall be installed on the building hereby approved. 
Reason: To protect the appearance of the building and accord with Local Plan policy LP2 coupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework 2023
Condition : 10 - Roof paraphernalia
No water tanks, plant, lift rooms or other permanent structures (unless otherwise shown on the approved plans listed above) shall be erected upon the roof of the approved building unless otherwise agreed in writing with the local planning authority.
Reason: To control the appearance of the building and safeguard the appearance of the area, in accordance with Local Plan policy LP1 coupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework 2023.
